post_text:
Don't forget this week's Parents in Partnership General Meeting.

Wednesday 6:30 PM

"Parents may think it could never happen in their home. Reality is that any device with internet accesses is a tool that predators can potentially use to access children.

Special guest, Jason Mitchell, who leads the Child Exploitation Investigations Group for the US Department of Homeland Security for the DFW area, will educate parents on how to protect our children and keep them safe from online predators.

The link to access the meeting will be added soon. The event will also be broadcast via Facebook Live.

Prize drawings for parents who attend the virtual meeting. There will be 24/7 playback available immediately following.

This is information you don't want to miss ... invite your family, friends, and neighbors to attend.

Read more about Jason Mitchell at www.imaginepip.org "

post_text:
#NTXGD is coming up on 9/17/2020 and our community has always been STRONG in showing support to faculty and staff through giving generously.

While some students return to campus next week, some remain #dragonsatadistance and this year we are introducing FUNdraising pages through Communities Foundation of Texas (CFT) - a perfect way to spread the word while we are distant!

We are asking faculty, staff, students, and families to build their own FUNdraising pages to share with family and friends, by email and on social media.

FUNdraising pages are easy to create and allow you to make a personal appeal to people you know.

Using this video for instructions, build your FUNdraising page to support Friends of Imagine North Texas today! See comments for the direct link to the giving page for YOUR school, click "Fundraise" and get started!

Early giving is open so you can share your page and donors can start giving TODAY!

Questions? Please contact advancement@imaginenorthtexas.org

How To Create Your FUNdraising Page

"Students and parents often weigh the value of an IB education against how well it prepares students for university admissions. Below are insights from several admissions teams on questions that often get asked about students applying to universities in the United States and Canada. While there is no secret formula for the perfect application at the college of your dreams, one thing is certain: IB students will have plenty to show universities as they prepare their applications."

Congratulations to Rhea Sood #classof2022 on her first place win in the 2020 Congressional Art Competition.

#Repost @repvantaylor with @get_repost
・・・
I'm happy to announce the winners of the 2020 Congressional Art Competition! Thank you to all who participated, as well as, their art teachers and support system. Every entry was incredible and unique. 🎨 • First Place: "Aged to Perfection" by Rhea Sood, McKinney’s Imagine International Academy
• Second Place: "Oppa" by Rachel Lee, Frisco’s Liberty High School
• Third Place: "A Day Captured" by Ananya Mahesh, Frisco’s Independence High School
• People's Choice: "Stone Guardians" by Ian Chen, Plano’s Jasper High School

post_text:
We interrupt this #seniorsunday to announce the online book fair starting tomorrow! Check our profile for the link or head over to Facebook. *
*
*
This year we will host our Spring Book Fair ONLINE!
Our fair will run April 27-May 10.
All book orders of more than $25 will be shipped for free to the address of your choice.
Toys and trinkets will have a shipping fee.
*****
We hope you use this time to stock your home library with books to read during the summer.
We appreciate your support. Profits from this fair will help purchase our Bluebonnet books for the 2020/2021 school year.

This week’s contest: the pets are so excited (and a bit confused) to have everyone home! Send in a photo of you and your pet. All pets welcome! Don’t have a pet? How about a favorite stuffed animal?

Requirements:
1.Photo submissions must include **Dragon NAME** and **GRADE**
2.By submitting photos, participants agree to have the photos posted on the school’s social media accounts.
3.Photos should be sent by noon each Friday. Winners drawn weekly on Friday afternoons.
4.New week’s theme will be posted on Sunday evening.
5.Send photos to: advancement@imaginenorthtexas.org

Questions? Contact Amy.Jones@imagineschools.org

post_text: We are excited to announce the 2020 Spring Musical: Bye Bye Birdie! If you like to act, sing, or dance then this is for you! Auditions are after school in Room 215 on February 27 and are open to Grades 6-12. All you have to do for the audition is sing a verse and chorus of your favorite Broadway or Disney song and read from the script. Stop by Room 215 for more information and to sign up for an audition time. Questions? Contact Amy.Jones@imagineschools.org

Thanksgiving Pies 2019
Friday, Nov 22nd

It is an Imagine tradition to celebrate Thanksgiving by sending home a pie/dessert with our teachers and staff to share with their families.
The PiP Teacher Appreciation Committee will be collecting pies and other desserts on Friday, November 22nd. Sign up below to indicate which pie/dessert that you'd like to donate.

Don't bake or want to hassle with drop off? Pies may be purchased for $10 from Tiers of Joy owned by Lauren Eaves (IIANT parent). She will make your pie and deliver it to the school for you. Contact her @ 469.288.8362.
